content: My name is Jussi Ikonen. Im a student here as Morden
this is the first time I am teaching in ORC
we are sure you can do a very good lesson today !
and as many of you know previous teachers at this deparment are way more experienced than I am =)
so I will need you all to participate so we will have a successfull lesson today =)
but none of them was in Poland :-)
first I want to thank yy dor this great opportunity to be here!
lets start with warming our fingers, shall we?

soo many students today! and Jerzy was fastest!
2 weeks ago there was a renju tournament called Baltic League
the tournament was played with Sakata rules and 50 min/player as timing
I'va heard Sakata rule has some defect ;)
it was my first live Sakata tourn =)
no defect was found at this tourn, because we had an extra rule, 4th and 5th move had to be inside 7x7 square
and after that 2 more inside 7x7 from the middle
today I will show few games from the tournament
I started my tourn with a lose against Olga and a win against Hans
at the third round I was against world top player, Stefan Karlsson
I had not prepared for this too much..
but I played already these 2 stones against Olga, and they seemed to be ok,
which one would you play? b or w?
I started this game wanting to get a draw
a win would not have been bad, but a draw would have been surely enough for me
so I played carefully at the beginning
doesn磘 look too bad for b, doesn磘 it?
at the point of 17. I saw Stefan was getting a little bothered
he took quite some time and made his 18!
because it would give him opportunity to keep on attacking
maybe.... that will be seen later on.,. =)
I did not find VCT for white
but b has potential to spread
so now I needed to deside do I want to win =)
RIGHT ; you had to make up your mind now
draw was an option no longer ...
I tought that for a bit
but could not find a good continuation
so as Im saying I was not playing well
it was a live tournament situation, and pretty stressfull for me
I should have just taken it cool
but now white has not too much
34 only need move m11,black has nothing
now he had only few minutes left
I may have a winning change
I thought I had a win, but looked wrong
and from no I had also less than 5 min
so no more moves on either of the protocols
we played some moves on lower right
and he won quite easily at upper left with app. 20 sec on his clock!
so what I want to teach you is to keep it cool =)
maybe one should not play for a fraw :)
no matter who is up against
many good cuts, but still awin afterall
but I belive still a win
I find this is win too...
it would have been guite a job to see it all in few minutes
I am here but was late
so after few minutes the game has ended
I was up against Joachim Gaulitz
and I had almost no fighting spirit left
so I will show that game also =)
what do you think of this?
I just put stones to the board
but he used guite a lot of time
and it seems 13 isn磘 too bad =)
I was arfaid that he would get it =)
again I was playing for a draw
seems you better now,why for draw
too tired from past games, maybe
he didn磘 have too much time anymore
so once again I was starting to go the same as last time
usually I do this kind of judgement mistakes
and the opponent just keeps attacking
but maybe it was just supposed to be like it =)
it seemed I was gettin the game bakc to myself
and I was playing on the edge, not the other way around =)
he was cool as ice, I was shakin
I could not belive my eyes!
so we went to a bar
for 15 minutes you would defend with it
not to lose to top players
but to lose it this way
1 point out of 4 at the first day
bad days happens - we will see on this weekend :-)
and it was known I had to play against Bj鰎n Lind on mornind
he is a bit better player than me also =)

i am here
i am here

I AM HERE
I AM HERE
we have time for one more
I was a bit tired from the night =)
you wanted to fill the board :)
this is where is went pretty naturally =)
haha, must store this in renlib
I was sure he would play down =)
and now I got a bit nervous again
38 - b7 a bit better, but looks like a win too
and I find 3x3 at the upper right
what was the sense of 41, hard to say
and won the last 2 games also =)
yea, you lose your mental control too easily still
thats the lesson today... no matter who is up against just take it cool
all BL2005 games can be found at www.nrc.renju.fi
We will see on this weekend
I wanna thank you all for a nice lesson!
